isoiec80000:term-t10-12.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "gyromagnetic ratio"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t10-12.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "magnetogyric ratio"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t10-12.1-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "gyromagnetic coefficient"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t10-12.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "gamma"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t10-12.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "10-12.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t10-12.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t10-12.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t10-12.1-2 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t10-12.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """proportionality constant between the magnetic dipole moment and the angular momentum:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
bb(ii(mu)) = gamma bb(ii(J))
++++

where

stem:[bb(ii(mu))]:: is the magnetic dipole moment (<<t10-9.1>>), and
stem:[bb(ii(J))]:: is the total angular momentum (<<t10-11>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """[stem%unnumbered]
++++
1 \"unitsml(A*m^2/(J*s))\" = 1 \"unitsml(A*s/kg)\" = 1 \"unitsml(T^(-1)*s^(-1))\"
++++

The systematic name is \"gyromagnetic coefficient\", but \"gyromagnetic ratio\" is more usual.

The gyromagnetic ratio of the proton is denoted by stem:[gamma_\"p\"].

The gyromagnetic ratio of the neutron is denoted by stem:[gamma_\"n\"].
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-A*m^2*J^(-1)*s^(-1) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-A*s/kg ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg^(-1)*s*A ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-10 .